ComicInfo.Summary:
MAD goes back to GHOUL! America’s longest-running satire magazine continues to scare the squares and poke fun at everything! This issue features a wide variety of classic MAD monstrous movie and terrifying TV parodies. Plus, spine-tingling vintage MAD pop culture spoofs and favorites like “Spy vs. Spy”, “MAD Look at...” by Sergio Aragonés, and much more from the Usual Gang of Idiots. Plus, a freaky new fold-in by Johnny Sampson, and eerie new cover art by Terry Wolfinger. MAD #33 will surely make your spine tingle with terrible tremors…of laughter.
